records.name: Nika Island Resort & Spa, Maldives

descriptions.direction: Located in Kudafolhudhoo, Nika Island Resort & Spa is in a rural area and on the beach. Nika Island Resort & Spa and Holi Faru Dive Site are worth checking out if an activity is on the agenda, while those wishing to experience the area's natural beauty can explore Ari Atoll and Feridhoo Beach. Looking to get your feet wet? Scuba diving, windsurfing and fishing adventures can be found near the property.
descriptions.general: Located in Kudafolhudhoo, Nika Island Resort & Spa is on the beach. Nika Island Resort & Spa and Feridhoo Harbor are worth checking out if an activity is on the agenda, while those wishing to experience the area's natural beauty can explore Mathiveri Finolhu and Maaya Thila. The beautiful 5-star Nika Island Resort & Spa, Maldives offers stand-alone beach or water villas surrounded by coral reefs. Private beaches, relaxing massage treatments and a gym are available. Exciting water sports like windsurfing, canoeing, and snorkeling can also be enjoyed here.The spacious air-conditioned villas are all equipped with a TV, CD player, an electric kettle, and a minibar. Chinese TV channels are available. There is also a living area with a sofa set. En suite bathrooms come with a shower and bathrobes, as well as free toiletries and slippers. Free WiFi is available in the rooms.Located in North Ari Atoll, Nika Island Resort & Spa, Maldives is about 72 km from Male International Airport in Malé. The resort will arrange round-trip seaplane transfers at an extra cost.Open-air dining with sea breeze can be enjoyed at the on-site restaurant, which serves Maldivian, Italian, and other international dishes. There are 2 bars which offer fine wine.
